==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philter
<hw>Phil"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>philtre</ets>, L. <ets>philtrum</ets>, Gr. <grk>fi`ltron</grk>, fr.
<grk>filei^n</grk> to love, <grk>fi`los</grk> dear, loving.]</ety>
<def>A potion or charm intended to excite the passion of love.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>philtre</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Philter
<hw>Phil"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Philtered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Philtering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To impregnate or
mix with a love potion; <as>as, to <ex>philter</ex> a
draught</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To charm to love; to excite to love or sexual desire
by a potion.</def> <rj><au>Gov. of Tongue.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phimosis</ent>⟦br⟧
